This Readme file contains the input and output tables used/generated from GChimera using the PhaseShift4 Matlab script

The input table involves creating the following 16 columns per residue:

Residue #
TOCSYHB2 Intensity
TOCSYHB3 Intensity
TOCSY Error
HN(CO)HBHB2 Intensity
HN(CO)HBHB3 Intensity
HN(CO)HB Error
HNHBHB2 Intensity
HNHBHB3 Intensity
HNHB Error
Residue One Letter Code (1-20)
Degenerate (1/0)
Phase Shift (1/0)
Φ Angle (°)
Ψ Angle (°)
Secondary Structure Characteristic (1-3)

In the case of beta branched resiudes, the experimental peak intensities for Hb2 and Hb3 become the same vakue

The resiude to number converion is:

G - 1
A - 2
V - 3
L - 4
I - 5
S - 6
T - 7
F - 8
Y - 9
H - 10
W - 11
C - 12
M - 13
K - 14
R - 15
N - 16
Q - 17
D - 18
E - 19
P - 20

The conversion is made due to a conversion issue Matlab has when uploading a table with letters,

Both the Degenerate and set phase shift to 0 have a 1/0 format where 1 represents a true statement whereas 0 represents a false statement.

In the case of Case Coefficients, Secondary Structure Characteristic can be set to be 1 for ɑ-helix, 2 for β-sheet, or 3 for averaged values. However, as was done with the GChimera experiment, the AutoCharacteristic (boolean found in the script) can be set in the script to true so that the Φ, Ψ angles are used to determine a characteristic.
Because of Autocharacteristic being set to true, the Secondary Structure Characteristic was set to 3 for GChimera since the Φ, Ψ angles were used instead
